SIMPLE: futurist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Futurist
<hw>Fu"tur*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One whose chief
interests are in what is to come; one who anxiously, eagerly, or
confidently looks forward to the future; an expectant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>One who believes or maintains
that the fulfillment of the prophecies of the Bible is to be in the
future.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Futuritial</ent>⟦br⟧
